{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "a6e50263-bfae-4adb-8ee8-06462e961fbb",
		"name": "Tyk Demo - Federation",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Federation - Users Posts",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
							"});",
							"",
							"pm.test(\"Users & Posts Data returned from Federated Graph\", function () {",
							"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.data.user.name).to.eql(\"Leanne Graham\");",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.data.user.posts.length).to.eql(10);",
							"});"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript"
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"method": "POST",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\"query\":\"query {\\n  user(id:1) {\\n    name\\n    posts {\\n      title\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\",\"variables\":null}"
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "http://{{tyk-gateway.host}}/social-media-apis-federated/",
					"protocol": "http",
					"host": [
						"{{tyk-gateway.host}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"social-media-apis-federated",
						""
					]
				},
				"description": "This GraphQL API illustrates, with a single request, the ability to combine 2 subgraphs into a single Federated graphQL API using Tyk\n\n**Subgraph URLs:**\n\n*   [http://localhost:4001/query](http://localhost:4001/query)\n*   [http://localhost:4002/query](http://localhost:4002/query)\n    \n\n**Query to send to supergraph:**\n\n``` graphql\nquery{\n  user(id: 1){\n    id\n    name\n    posts{\n      id\n      title\n    }\n}\n\n```\n\nCheckout the federation deployment README for steps to adding a 3rd subgraph"
			},
			"response": []
		}
	],
